Day-15 Notes – Video Application Deployment using Docker, GitHub & Helm
1️⃣ Helm Installation

Sabse pehle server par Helm install kiya.

wget https://get.helm.sh/helm-v3.14.0-linux-amd64.tar.gz
tar -zxvf helm-v3.14.0-linux-amd64.tar.gz
mv linux-amd64/helm /usr/local/bin/helm
helm version
2️⃣ Video File Preparation

Video file ko GitHub repository me upload kiya.

Server par wget command se video download kiya.

3️⃣ Docker Project Folder

Ek folder banaya:

mkdir video-app
cd video-app
4️⃣ Docker me 3 files create ki

Docker project me 3 files create ki:

video-app
 ├── Dockerfile
 ├── index.html
 └── video.mp4
Dockerfile

Container ke liye Dockerfile banaya jisme Nginx use kiya.

index.html

HTML file create ki jisme video play hota hai.

video.mp4

Application ke liye video file use ki.

5️⃣ Docker Image Build

Docker image build ki:

docker build -t ajaypatel001/video-app:v1 .
6️⃣ Docker Hub Login

Docker Hub me login kiya:

docker login

Username aur password enter kiya.

7️⃣ Docker Image Push

Image ko Docker Hub me push kiya:

docker push ajaypatel001/video-app:v1
8️⃣ Helm Chart Creation

Helm chart create kiya:

helm create project-1

Isse Helm chart ka structure create ho gaya.

9️⃣ values.yaml Configuration

values.yaml me Docker image repository aur tag update kiya.

image:
  repository: ajaypatel001/video-app
  tag: v1
  pullPolicy: IfNotPresent

Service type ko NodePort / LoadBalancer set kiya.

🔟 Application Deployment using Helm

Application deploy ki:

helm install video project-1
1️⃣1️⃣ Deployment Verification

Pods check kiye:

kubectl get pods

Services check ki:

kubectl get svc
1️⃣2️⃣ Result

Video application Kubernetes cluster me successfully deploy ho gayi.

Browser ke through service URL se video play hua.
